[{"short_id":"yaufia","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yaufia","created_at":"2021-09-18T17:11:01.000-05:00","title":"Is the formal methods winter about to end?","url":"","score":28,"flags":1,"comment_count":13,"description":"\u003cp\u003eFormal methods (theorem proving, model checking, static analysis, abstract interpretation, advanced type systems, program semantics, etc) have remained a relatively niche topic during the last two and a half decades. The field saw much interest during the 1980s and early 1990s. \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tony_Hoare#Apologies_and_retractions\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003eTony Hoare‚Äôs 1996 speech\u003c/a\u003e recognized formal methods were so far unable to scale to real-world software, and that event perhaps marked the beginning of a formal methods winter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDo you think the field is starting to regain attention? I have observed many positive indicators:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStrong interest in the mathematics community to mechanize proofs, driven by Lean\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSome technical milestones, such as end-to-end proofs carried by the DeepSpec project\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEmerging synergies with AI, e.g. synthesis\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSome job openings in mainstream companies, e.g. Google\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRespectable number of grant calls and studentships related to the topic, growing from close to zero\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFunded work by cryptocurrency platforms to verify smart contracts, after multi-million fiascos\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs this a promising field to work on? What advances do you expect during this decade?\u003c/p\u003e\n","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yaufia/is_formal_methods_winter_about_end","submitter_user":{"username":"nextos","created_at":"2020-01-11T16:18:52.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"","is_moderator":false,"karma":57,"avatar_url":"/avatars/nextos-100.png","invited_by_user":"bandali"},"tags":["ask","formalmethods"]},{"short_id":"jmjlvj","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/jmjlvj","created_at":"2021-09-19T08:56:30.000-05:00","title":"Rust on the MOS 6502: Beyond Fibonacci","url":"https://gergo.erdi.hu/blog/2021-09-18-rust_on_the_mos_6502__beyond_fibonacci/","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/jmjlvj/rust_on_mos_6502_beyond_fibonacci","submitter_user":{"username":"calvin","created_at":"2014-07-01T06:47:13.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Soon we will all have special names... names designed to make the cathode ray tube resonate.","is_moderator":false,"karma":83525,"avatar_url":"/avatars/calvin-100.png","invited_by_user":"nbyouri","github_username":"NattyNarwhal"},"tags":["rust"]},{"short_id":"wfmjcc","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/wfmjcc","created_at":"2021-09-18T05:50:06.000-05:00","title":"DOS Subsystem for Linux","url":"https://github.com/haileys/doslinux","score":36,"flags":0,"comment_count":21,"description":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/wfmjcc/dos_subsystem_for_linux","submitter_user":{"username":"raymii","created_at":"2013-11-20T11:58:43.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"üêã\r\nhttps://raymii.org","is_moderator":false,"karma":12289,"avatar_url":"/avatars/raymii-100.png","invited_by_user":"journeysquid"},"tags":["linux"]},{"short_id":"hdmuth","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hdmuth","created_at":"2021-09-18T21:43:24.000-05:00","title":"The DragonFlyBSD Operating System (2004)","url":"https://people.freebsd.org/~hsu/publications/dragonflybsd.asiabsdcon04.pdf","score":8,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hdmuth/dragonflybsd_operating_system_2004","submitter_user":{"username":"tobin_baker","created_at":"2019-1